-- Deutsche Bank’s Private Wealth Management Division Hires Apffel
-- B y   A a r o n   K i r c h f e l d
-- 2010-10-08T08:30:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/deutsche-bank-s-private-wealth-management-hires-apffel-to-head-investments.html
Deutsche Bank AG’s private wealth
management unit named Arnaud Apffel of Lombard Odier Darier
Hentsch & Cie. the head of global investment solutions for
Europe, the Middle East and Africa.  Apffel, who is based in Geneva, will oversee global
investment solutions activities across all asset classes for the
region, according to an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Aaron Kirchfeld at 
 akirchfeld@bloomberg.net  